<BaseLayout title="Funding and Conflicts | CourtScope"><section class="hero"><div class="prose-width"><p class="eyebrow">Public policy</p><h1>Funding and Conflicts</h1><p class="lede">CourtScope currently has no funders, donations, sponsors, advertisers, or organizational conflicts.</p></div></section><section class="section"><div class="prose-width"><div class="card"><p>All future organizational funding will be disclosed publicly. No funder, sponsor, advertiser, candidate, judge, court, or political organization may control scores, source admission, corrections, or methodology.</p><h2>What controls</h2><p>Official source terms, applicable law, dataset-specific notices, and the current published CourtScope methodology control where they are more specific. Contact <a href="mailto:info@courtscope.org">info@courtscope.org</a> for questions.</p><p><strong>Last updated:</strong> July 11, 2026</p></div></div></section></BaseLayout>